docs.abstract: In order to be of use, assistants like Cortana and Siri need to know a lot about you. Reading the companies’ privacy statements can give you an idea of how much.
docs.snippet: In order to be of use, assistants like Cortana and Siri need to know a lot about you. Reading the companies’ privacy statements can give you an idea of how much.
docs.lead_paragraph: Q. I was going to try Cortana, Microsoft’s version of Siri, but to use it, you have to allow Microsoft access to your location, your contacts, voice input, information from email and text messages, browser history, search history, calendar details “and other information.” Naturally, I declined. Why does Microsoft need so much personal information and what does Microsoft do with it?

headline.main: Protecting Personal Information From Virtual Assistants
headline.print_headline: The Data Needs of Virtual Assistants
